<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFC66A79F82192EE167BBE44" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFC66A79F82192EE167BBE44" blockId="61.[2013,2609,1089,1516]" pageId="61" pageNumber="819">
Alternatively treated in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79F6B892EE17B8BFEA" box="[2372,2488,1207,1240]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Eptesicus</taxonomicName>
or Nycterikaupius but here placed in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79F65892861431BE32" box="[2468,2609,1247,1280]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neoromicia</taxonomicName>
based on bacular morphology. Previously considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79F67493771429BE7D" baseAuthorityName="A. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[2440,2601,1326,1359]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">N. capensis</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
